column1: # Figures for 1823, 1824 and 1825 use months running from the 26th of one month to 25th of the next, and have been omitted.
# Figures for 1864 duplicate the 1864 figures for the Boston Grand Sluice site, and have been omitted.
# The duplicate figures possibly relate to the period between observers Mr Veall and Dr Mercer Adams.
# The comment on the 1870s sheet that the gauge moved to High Street in 1872 is confusing.
# The sheets for the High Street site (Mr Wheeler) show that gauge coming from Pen Street slightly earlier in 1872.
